<br>
AOW Rule:<br>
<br>
The AOW may only be attempted upon your turn at the Statue. <br>
<br>
Planes, Fear, Sky, Hate:<br>
<br>
Going into a plane on a day that another guild has it reserved without their permission will be assessed the same 30 day penalty.<br>
<br>
TOV and multiple mob rots:<br>
<br>
When a guild gets onto a rotation, it is not acceptable for another guild to go in after they are done and clean up what is left. any guild caught doing so will be assessed the penalty of losing their current rot turn and next rot turn on said rotation if they are not on said rotation a suitable punishment will be worked out on a case by case basis.<br>
<br>
Entering the Glyphed/Exiled/Cursed rotation.<br>
<br>
A force of 40 members must be in the zone before the first taskmaster is killed for the rotation guild to back off and allow you an attempt. Any killing to stall will not be tolerated. Gaining access to the rotation is only done by killing both the Glyphed and Exiled on one Turn, you cannot do a Exiled after someone else has done the Glyphed and his PH has respawned. If you fail to the Gylphed or Exiled or are unable to spawn them they will pass to the guild that is up for the kill on rotation.<br>
<br>
Cursed rules:<br>
<br>
Upon entering the Glyphed/Exiled rotation a guild may make 2 attempts at killing cursed on their day of the cycle. These attempts must be done first thing upon the mobs being known up and if unsuccessful should let the guild currently up for cleanup or an RTA admin know. These attempts can only be done on your turn at the Glyphed/Exiled spawn, not at any other time unless ffa is called on the mobs. <br>
<br>
Ssra Basement Etiquette:<br>
<br>
Basically, if the 2 Rhoz's are up please stay out of the mines. The 2 rhoz's and taskmasters are triggers for the G/E/C cycle and killing them can screw it up.<br>
<br>
In other words, any day that the G/E/C is due it is requested that only the Guild on Rotation, or the Guild attempting to enter the Rotation, enter the basement. Although it is possible to do the mines without killing any of the trigger mobs it is too easy for someone to screw it up and staying out is the convention.  <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Have a Nice Day - Management</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theadmin@therathetravelagency>TheAdmin</A> at: 4/8/03 9:04:47 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showPrevMessage?topicID=245.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showNextMessage?topicID=245.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.emailToFriend?topicID=245.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.threadControl?topicID=245.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=245.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetra